destiny /ˈdɛstɪnɪ/

(destinies) 

1. N-COUNT A person's destiny is everything that happens to them during their life, including what will happen in the future, especially when it is considered to be controlled by someone or something else. 命运 

例： We are masters of our own destiny. 我们是自己命运的主人。 

2. N-UNCOUNT Destiny is the force which some people believe controls the things that happen to you in your life. 天数; 定数 

